precedented times. Man, those were the days.</p><p>Horror movies aren&#8217;t my jam, and neither are haunted houses, but people still need to get their kicks, and in Tokyo, that means a visit to Kowagarasetai, a Japanese haunted house and horror event production company.</p><p>Roughly translated, Kowagarasetai means &#8216;the Scaredy Squad&#8217;.</p><p>They claim the concept is the first of its kind, according to <a href="https://www.msn.com/en-us/health/medical/the-world-s-first-drive-in-haunted-house-is-in-tokyo-and-it-s-terrifying/ar-BB17Wm3O?li=BBnba9O" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">MSN</a>:</p><blockquote><p>&#8220;With the virus, I knew there would be no way we could have a traditional haunted house, with all that screaming in a small confined space,&#8221; Kenta Iwana, Kowagarasetai&#8217;s founder, said&#8230;</p><p>&#8220;When I read that drive-through theaters were making a comeback, it was my &#8216;aha&#8217; moment.&#8221;</p></blockquote><p>Great, now I have <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=djV11Xbc914" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">a-ha&#8217;s &#8216;Take On Me&#8217;</a> stuck in my head, and so do you.</p><p>The haunted house is located in a covered parking garage in downtown Tokyo, and the experience of driving through is supposed to simulate what it would be like to be stuck in a car during a zombie outbreak.</p><p>For an extra fee, those who don&#8217;t have a car can rent one, and there&#8217;s the option for an extra-bloody package, too.</p><p>Let&#8217;s see some footage from the house, and hear from Kenta:</p><p><iframe loading="lazy" src="about:blank" width="640" height="360" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen" data-rocket-lazyload="fitvidscompatible" data-lazy-src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/LKcgod3lyfQ"><span data-mce-type="bookmark" style="display: inline-block; width: 0px; overflow: hidden; line-height: 0;" class="mce_SELRES_start">﻿</span></iframe><noscript><iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/LKcgod3lyfQ" width="640" height="360" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"><span data-mce-type="bookmark" style="display: inline-block; width: 0px; overflow: hidden; line-height: 0;" class="mce_SELRES_start">﻿</span></iframe></noscript></p><p>The temptation to wind down a window and throat punch someone would be extreme.</p><p>More on how it all works:</p><blockquote><p>Drivers receive a set of Bluetooth speakers and the spooky tale begins.</p><p>&#8220;Around these parts, there&#8217;s a legend that the ghosts attack humans. Honk your horn three times if you want to hear more,&#8221; says the voice from the speaker, in Japanese.</p><p>For the next 17 minutes, blood-soaked ghouls and zombies press up against the windows and rock the car.</p></blockquote><p>Once you&#8217;re done, the company will clean your car so that you don&#8217;t get horrified looks on the highway.</p><p>Reports suggest demand is high, and Kenta claims there is currently a waiting list of around 1 000 people.</p><p>I guess you have to hand it to them for a successful COVID-19 pivot.</p><p>[source:<a href="https://www.msn.com/en-us/health/medical/the-world-s-first-drive-in-haunted-house-is-in-tokyo-and-it-s-terrifying/ar-BB17Wm3O?li=BBnba9O" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">msn</a>]</p></div><ul class="next-prev-post-nav"><li> &larr; <a href="https://www.2oceansvibe.com/2020/08/14/upcoming-docuseries-takes-deep-dive-into-the-history-of-gaming-trailer/" rel="prev">Upcoming Docuseries Takes Deep Dive Into The History Of Gaming [Trailer]</a></li><li> <a href="https://www.2oceansvibe.com/2020/08/14/you-can-own-this-immaculate-1987-bentley-sedan-for-r400k/" rel="next">You Can Own This Immaculate 1987 Bentley Sedan For R400k</a> &rarr;</li></ul><div class="post-meta clearfix"><ul class="social"><li class="twitter"> <a href="httsp://twitter.com/share" class="twitter-share-button" data-count="none" data-url="https://www.2oceansvibe.com/2020/08/14/tokyo-drive-in-haun